snippet.textDisplay: Can't fault the effort today - and anyone doubting that Jose isnt a good manager just take a look at how he set us up today. And but for the miss of the season we'd have got something today. But this doesn't altar the fact that in the space of a year we've gone from being the only team in the league that could seriously challenge the likes of city and Liverpool to being a side happy to run a top side close. Gone from being a team that's been a shoe-in for top 4 to an Everton or west ham. Questions need to be asked how we've sunk so far so quickly? Who at the club decided to leave us with only one out and out striker? Did no one at the club notice our league results were relegation form after February? Who made the decision to make one of our few signings in the summer a player who can't even get in the leeds side? A year ago this club had the world at its feet - and we've blown it big time. We can certainly forget about the top 4 - unless we add some quality to this squad pronto will be surprised if we even make top 6. Apparently Bruno fernandes would sign tomorrow - what the eff are we waiting for?

snippet.textDisplay: If you're satisfied and happy about a performance like that, it's no wonder other teams are winning the trophies. Liverpool were far away from their best today and controlled the game when they wanted to. Spurs didn't create chances, Liverpool handed almost every single one of those chances to them. Gomez misjudging a long ball, Wijnaldum just stumbling it away and so on. Spurs finishing ability was horrendous again. Since the beginning of the season there is absolutely no tactics to be found. Guys are in different positions every 5 minutes, the team doesn't attack in unity nor defend in unity, that's what the best teams like Liverpool do. From a team which was in the Champions League final last year it's sad to see most people are happy about this performance. A great Tottenham team would have at least tied or even won that game.
